Today is 12 years of Dogecoin ( $DOGE)

Exactly 12 years ago, on December 6, 2013, Billy Markus and Jackson Palmer launched Dogecoin in just a couple of hours. It was meant as pure satire  a friendly joke on Bitcoin and crypto hype, built around the viral " $DOGE" Shiba Inu meme.

 3 quick facts about Dogecoin:
 
1. Elon Musk started tweeting about  $DOGE in 2019, calling it his "fav cryptocurrency" ‚Äî single tweets still move the price by double-digit percent in 2025.  
 
2. Unlike Bitcoin, Dogecoin is inflationary: ~5 billion new coins are minted every year, keeping fees tiny and making it perfect for tipping and micro-payments.  
 
3. It survived a massive Christmas 2013 hack, multiple boom-bust cycles, and still sits comfortably in the top-10 by trading volume and market cap (~$20-25B in 2025).
